Bernard Kabanda Sslongo (1959 – 4 September 1999) was an Ugandan guitarist.

He had just realised fame in the world music circuit through his appearances at WOMAD in the USA and the UK in 1999 before he died of AIDS less than two months after his performance at Womad's Reading festival, aged only 40.
